vintage.name: Vintage But New Peyote Bird Designs Watch, Necklace, Bracelet
vintage.description: I had a southwest store in Sonoma County years ago and closed it in 1995. I personally went to New Mexico in the 1980s and early 1990s and worked with the Native American Indians and southwest artisans for this Peyote Bird Designs vintage but new hand beaded artisan watch bracelet, necklace and 5 strand bracelet.  Peyote Bird Designs is out of Santa Fe, New Mexico.  Beautiful Peyote Bird watch has a hand crafted band signed by Don Lucas. The watch and necklace also has Peyote Bird Designs Hallmark stamped on the back of watch and on a charm on the necklace showing that it is a Peyote Bird Designs original.The vintage but new watch has been in storage since 1995 and has never been worn and is still in it's original box as you can see in the photos in this ad.   So it is vintage but new.  I also have a beautifully handcrafted matching necklace and bracelet.  These can be bought as a set or purchased separately.  There is a discount if more than one item is purchased. The Peyote Bird watch has a triple strand beaded band with genuine Amethyst and Onyx and other types of beads, one with small heart, star and flower sterling silver charms signed Don Lucas.   Watch and band components, charms etc are sterling silver.   The chain at one end makes the watch size adjustable and has a tiny Peyote Bird charm marked sterling, the other end has a hook to loop through the chain to fasten the band.   The third item is a Peyote Bird Designs beaded bracelet with black, white and silver with some purple very old beads has an African theme with an elephant, lion, hippo and zebra sterling silver charms.  The clasp is a authentic Indian head nickel.  Bracelet is vintage but new.  Never worn.The watch currently needs a battery that I can take care of once the watch is sold.   The watch and band are very sturdy and unique.  The band has hand tooled sterling silver, multi semi precious stones plus two charms have Onyx stones mounted in them as well as the stem for winding the watch also has Onyx. The watch face is 1 1/8 wide including stem. This western charm watch bracelets length is about 7 but can be made larger by using the additional chain links.  The watch band is a standout to layer with your Peyote Bird beaded bracelet, jewel tone or silver bracelets.   Made by Don Lucas and sold by Sundance in the 1980's and 1990's, it is a stunner. Hallmark stamped on back of watch.  Quartz Timepiece.  The watch will come in the original box. The negatives:The air bag recall needs to be done, and the seatbelt receiver replaced (both will be done for free at the dealer, I just never got around to it because its a few cities away)Dings on body (see passenger door) and minor visual defects on exterior (rock chips front bumper) 20 year old black car, its super clean and representable but its also not a complete garage queen.Will need tires soon. loud.name: Basson Sound - Speaker Monitor
loud.description: Basson Sound - Speaker MonitorUp for sale is a good condition, used Basson Speaker. Built for low frequences and high volume.The Basson B412 guitar cab is designed for smooth tone at extreme volume. The enclosure is air sealed with silicone to maintain consistent air volume, creating an air spring to prevent the audio speaker from excess travel. The result is less speaker distortion when you play low and loud. This consistency combined with 300W of power handling makes for a cab low enough for the 7-string enthusiast, and clear enough for the clean tone soloist. An amazing 480W output. Removable casters.B412 Guitar Cabinet Specifications:* 4x12 Eminence Legends* 300W power handling* 8 ohms* 101dB* 30-1/2W x 34-1/4H x 14-1/4D* 106 lbs.FEATURES* Incredibly smooth tone* Air sealed with silicon* All joints reinforced with a 1-1/4 brace* Tolex covered cabinet* 2 recessed metal 1/4 inputs* Removable wheels

famous.name: Famous FS-1 Soprano Ukulele OBO
famous.description: Pretty little soprano, nice build with super-thin mahogany laminate, but with a sound that will rival most sold-wood ukes. Extremely light, with excellent projection and beautiful resonance. The FS-1 is a Japanese build, identical to the Kiwaya KS-1, but sold only to the Japanese market. This older uke has a Rosewood fingerboard, which you won't find in production any longer...the newer ones are walnut.  Nice, low action and great intonation. Friction tuners. Tiny scratch on the headstock, mark on the first fret - see the photos for detail. One-of-a-kind cloth gig bag included. Reasonable offers are welcome.
